# CHANGELOG.md is managed by release-please (googleapis/release-please-action).
# release-please generates its release sections in its own markdown style,
# which prettier then reformats — every release PR failed the
# `pre-commit · all hooks` check on a prettier CHANGELOG reflow, and manual
# `[Unreleased]` edits hit the same reflow churn (caught 4+ times in CI
# across batches). The CHANGELOG is prose; prettier adds ~no value there.
# Ignoring it ends that whole class of failure and keeps release-please's
# output authoritative.
CHANGELOG.md

# Helm chart templates (slice 038) embed Go-template `{{ ... }}` directives
# that are NOT valid YAML — prettier would mangle the control flow and the
# `nindent` whitespace that Helm rendering depends on. The pure-YAML chart
# files (Chart.yaml, values.yaml, values-production.yaml) stay
# prettier-managed; only templates/ and NOTES.txt are ignored.
deploy/helm/templates/
